# Reflection

## What I Learned

Hallucinations often appear in clusters rather than isolation. A single AI response may combine fabricated studies, invented organizations, unsupported statistics, false expert attributions, and misleading recommendations. Effective evaluation requires assessing every factual claim independently while considering the potential impact on users.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For future evaluations, I would verify every cited organization, statistic, researcher, and recommendation against authoritative sources before accepting them. I would also distinguish between established scientific evidence, emerging research, expert opinion, and unsupported speculation.

